Steep Decline with Small Discounts üìâ: As soon as discounts are introduced, even at a modest level (around 10%), there‚Äôs a sharp drop in total profit. This suggests that even small discounts can significantly impact the bottom line, likely because they reduce the margin without sufficiently increasing sales volume to compensate.

